EATS REVIEW: Tatsunoko Bento-ya at FB Homes Paranaque

VERDICT: 3/5

COMMENTS: 
I ordered katsudon. Pork was dry and it's like something your mom tried cooking for the first time. Presentation was sakto lang The restaurant looks like an extra room in a house converted to serve such a function. However, what I like is the super fast service. When I say super fast it is less than 10 minutes. The staff were warm and it is easy to get a table. This is okay if you have craving for Japanese food at a super affordable price. What I ate just cost 170php and there is no service charge. I saw some appetizers in the menu which cost as low as 60php. If you are used to fine dining though, this is not recommended since the taste is just totally average. Another good thing though is that this will be sure to fill you up since the serving is a lot...like almost 2x the serving of Tokyo Tokyo.
